<br>
Snee <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ukeziahthotep.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Keziah Thotep</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/1/02 10:35:34 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3870.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What is the benefit of wpn skill above your level?</span><hr size=1> To best of my knowledge, as you raise your weapon skill to 50, it will raise your max damage.  Over 50 weapon skill will bring your minimum damage up. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uaureliuscov.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aurelius CoV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/1/02 10:44:09 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3870.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What is the benefit of wpn skill above your level?</span><hr size=1> Every point counts a little bit :) <p><center><br>"I am still learning" <br>
- Michelangelo</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uwrathog777.showPublicProfile?language=EN>WrathOG777</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/1/02 10:53:15 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3870.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What is the benefit of wpn skill above your level?</span><hr size=1> Skill above your lvl is identical to the benefit until you get below your lvl.  Each point added to weapon makes you a little better.  <br>
<br>
I rate skill/attribute/qual/bonus vs damage to enemys.  Each point (using what I know, however little that may be) gives you...<br>
1 skill = 1.5%<br>
1 attribute = 0.5%    *above 200 you get demishing returns.<br>
1 qual/bonus = 1% <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ujammermon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jammermon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/2/02 11:05:13 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3870.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What is the benefit of wpn skill above your level?</span><hr size=1> Some Skills do help... <br>
<br>
Envenom you CAN use higher poisons... So if you are L25 with Skill trained 25 and +5 envenom you CAN use the Skill 30 envenom. <br>
<br>
Critical Strike... Mythic has announced that Crit Strike over 50 does add to Crit Strike damage... but about 1/3 of the bonus before. Below L50 each CS Train adds +9 Damage to Maximum, which averages 4.5, only affects Crit Strike moves. <br>
<br>
Weapon... None. Far as anyone knows the 100% of level is the high ceiling; 105% of level does nothing. <br>
<br>
Stealth... It is FELT that being over trained doesn't really affect being spotted BUT does affect how far you spot another. So being 3 over level lets you see an Assasin 1/2 the length of a horse further away and a non-assassin stealther the enitire length of the horse farther.<br>
<br>
Hope that helps. In general the little bit you get on the skills is not worth going over 100% of level. <br>
<br>
Jammer <p>Jammer Mon
